abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday he had spoken with Chinese President Xi Jinping and the United States was working very closely with China on the coronavirus outbreak.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday he had spoken with Chinese President Xi Jinping and the United States was working very closely with China on the coronavirus outbreak.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday he had spoken with Chinese President Xi Jinping and the United States was working very closely with China on the coronavirus outbreak.
headline_main: Trump Says He Spoke to China's Xi, U.S. Working Closely With China on Coronavirus
headline_print_headline: Trump Says He Spoke to China's Xi, U.S. Working Closely With China on Coronavirus

abstract: The United Kingdom leaves the European Union an hour before midnight on Friday, casting off into an uncertain Brexit future  that also challenges Europe's post-World War Two project of forging unity from the ruins of conflict.
snippet: The United Kingdom leaves the European Union an hour before midnight on Friday, casting off into an uncertain Brexit future  that also challenges Europe's post-World War Two project of forging unity from the ruins of conflict.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The United Kingdom leaves the European Union an hour before midnight on Friday, casting off into an uncertain Brexit future that also challenges Europe's post-World War Two project of forging unity from the ruins of conflict.
headline_main: Into the Brexit Unknown, a Dis-United Kingdom Exits the European Union
headline_print_headline: Into the Brexit Unknown, a Dis-United Kingdom Exits the European Union

abstract: Most presidential candidates try to manage expectations in the final stretch of a campaign knowing a surprise win is always better than an expected one. Not Bernie Sanders.
snippet: Most presidential candidates try to manage expectations in the final stretch of a campaign knowing a surprise win is always better than an expected one. Not Bernie Sanders.
lead_paragraph: SIOUX CITY, Iowa — Most presidential candidates try to manage expectations in the final stretch of a campaign knowing a surprise win is always better than an expected one. Not Bernie Sanders.
headline_main: 'How Good I Feel': Sanders Setting High Expectations in Iowa
headline_print_headline: 'How Good I Feel': Sanders Setting High Expectations in Iowa

abstract: Democratic officials and some activists for the candidate say Joe Biden’s Iowa organization is weak in some areas, which could hurt him on caucus night. Biden aides say they have plenty of boots on the ground.
snippet: Democratic officials and some activists for the candidate say Joe Biden’s Iowa organization is weak in some areas, which could hurt him on caucus night. Biden aides say they have plenty of boots on the ground.
lead_paragraph: DUBUQUE, Iowa — This city on the bluffs of the Mississippi River, which rose as a hub of furniture-making and brewing, ought to be a stronghold for Joseph R. Biden Jr. It is a blue-collar enclave with a Catholic heritage, aligning with his working class pitch to voters. Its 31-year-old, labor-connected congresswoman, Abby Finkenauer, has endorsed Mr. Biden.

abstract: Lawyers defending U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial wrapped up their presentation on Tuesday.
snippet: Lawyers defending U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial wrapped up their presentation on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Lawyers defending U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial wrapped up their presentation on Tuesday.

abstract: That could change as the questioning continues.
snippet: That could change as the questioning continues.
lead_paragraph: Asked why Republican senators addressed almost all of their questions to President Trump’s lawyers and Democratic senators to the House managers, Senator Mike Braun, Republican of Indiana, had a simple answer: “You want to control the dynamic,” he said.
headline_main: Senators are happy to ask questions they already know the answers to.

abstract: The landscape has shifted so much that a proposal that would have been a nonstarter a decade ago has put the Palestinian leader Mahmoud Abbas in a bind.
snippet: The landscape has shifted so much that a proposal that would have been a nonstarter a decade ago has put the Palestinian leader Mahmoud Abbas in a bind.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — For Mahmoud Abbas, the ailing octogenarian president of the Palestinian Authority, his life’s work — a viable state side-by-side with Israel — is quickly slipping away.

abstract: The U.S. Interior Department is grounding its fleet of about 800 Chinese-made drones but will allow their use for emergency situations, the department said on Wednesday.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Interior Department is grounding its fleet of about 800 Chinese-made drones but will allow their use for emergency situations, the department said on Wednesday.
